MUST HAVE
As a student, I want a "quick" way to log my daily feelings so I can monitor my stress without spending too much time. 
As a student experiencing a mental health crisis, I want immediate access to a 24/7 emergency hotline so that I can get help instantly.
As a busy student with back-to-back classes, I want to log my mood using simple emojis so that I can track my mental well-being in under five minutes.
As a Taylor's student, I want to book appointments with campus counselors (like Joshua or Zig) directly in the app. 
As a user concerned about stigma, I want my data to remain 100% anonymous so that I feel safe sharing my true feelings 

SHOULD HAVE
As a student feeling isolated by academic pressure, I want to participate in an anonymous sharing community so that I can connect with peers facing similar challenges.
As a student practicing self-reflection, I want a private diary and notes page so that I can record my thoughts "strictly for my eyes only".

COULD HAVE
As a stressed student before an exam, I want to listen to "Lakeside Zen" or nature sounds so that I can calm my mind and improve my focus.
As a student studying late at night, I want to use a dark-mode interface so that the app is comfortable to use without straining my eyes.

WONT HAVE
As a student, I want to have a video call with a counselor directly in the app, so that I don't have to travel to the Block B office.
As a student, I want the app to automatically diagnose my mental health condition, so that I can understand my symptoms immediately
As a student, I want to link my Taylor's app profile to my Instagram, so that I can share my mood updates with my friends.
